"We did it. We all did it." @AstroDrewMorgan thanks the science and mission teams on a successful series of spacewalks. The third spacewalk of the year concluded at 1:20pm ET, making it 6 hours and 16 minutes in length. Stay updated: https://t.co/FRrjhINIvY https://t.co/vZozyUQNuM

✅ Mission milestone achieved!

@BaseballPoodle @shawnlonghofer @AstroDrewMorgan @esa @astro_luca @Space_Station This pup nose how to get our attention.🤩

@astrondrew Thank you for watching with us! 💫

@JulietteMajor Thanks for watching with us! https://t.co/DAgQfRQHjx

🕠 Watch live at 5:30am ET: https://t.co/ZuxLDtRxxM https://t.co/CoGEKaLqAK

The hottest of hot Jupiters are the strangest of faraway exoplanets, according to new findings from our @NASASpitzer telescope. The heat on this kind of planet is so extreme, planetwide meltdowns tear apart the molecules that make up the atmosphere: https://t.co/40fJN4PuN2 https://t.co/0O1Nbx8C3N
